00070 /*
00071  * Maximum number of aperture parameters is set by the outline aperture
00072  * macro. There (p. 28) is defined up to 50 points in polygon.

00074  */

00227 /* Used for HID attributes (exporting and printing, mostly).
00228    HA_boolean uses int_value, HA_enum sets int_value to the index and
00229    str_value to the enumeration string.  HID_Label just shows the
00230    default str_value.  HID_Mixed is a real_value followed by an enum,
00231    like 0.5in or 100mm. 
00232 */
00233 typedef struct {
00234     int int_value;
00235     char *str_value;
00236     double real_value;
00237 } gerbv_HID_Attr_Val;
00238 
00239 typedef struct {
00240     char *name;
00241     char *help_text;
00242     enum
00243        { HID_Label, HID_Integer, HID_Real, HID_String,
00244          HID_Boolean, HID_Enum, HID_Mixed, HID_Path
00245        } type;
00246     int min_val, max_val;   /* for integer and real */
00247     gerbv_HID_Attr_Val default_val;       /* Also actual value for global attributes.  */
00248     const char **enumerations;
00249     /* If set, this is used for global attributes (i.e. those set
00250        statically with REGISTER_ATTRIBUTES below) instead of changing
00251        the default_val.  Note that a HID_Mixed attribute must specify a
00252        pointer to gerbv_HID_Attr_Val here, and HID_Boolean assumes this is
00253        "char *" so the value should be initialized to zero, and may be
00254        set to non-zero (not always one).  */
00255     void *value;
00256     int hash; /* for detecting changes. */
00257 } gerbv_HID_Attribute;
00258 /* end of HID attributes from PCB */
